<br>
I'm not sure why I'm continuing this.  But what the heck:<br>
<br>
From your first post, the one you linked to.  &quot;If you have any questions about this guild after you have seen the link above, please email me at siteservant@hotmail.com, or contact me in Norrath, though depending on what I am doing, I may not be free answer your tells immediately.&quot;<br>
<br>
You asked for questions.  Now granted, I replied to the thread rather than going directly to you but I wasn't the first.  Vallerian Wintermyst, was the first reply and he (she?) raised the same question I did.  When you post on a community message board you must expect replies.<br>
<br>
&quot;You are an offense to me and anyone else who does not have everything exactly the way YOU want it. God, for bid we were to be on YOUR RP server and play the way we want.&quot;<br>
<br>
That's reading a lot into what I say.  I've never said I want my standards to be adopted.  I've said I want people to discuss what their standards are.  We all evaluate the game and our social interaction on many levels.  Some things we like, some things we don't.  An open, frank discussion of what every one likes and doesn't like might help build a stronger community and help keep all players as satisfied as possible.  It is not my server but it is OUR server, the server we have chosen, the server that could fail if too many people give up in frustration.<br>
<br>
&quot;Maybe it would be best if you post your rules, and the exact way you want everyone to be. Then, hopefully, if we all complied, we would never again have to see you on these message boards.&quot;<br>
<br>
Posting rules is not something I'd do.  Posting what I like and don't like about the server and encouraging others to do so in the same thread could be helpful though.  I may do that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showMessageRange?topicID=1403.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showMessageRange?topicID=1403.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showMessageRange?topicID=1403.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a> <b>4</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showPrevMessage?topicID=1403.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showNextMessage?topicID=1403.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1403.topic&index=63><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.threadControl?topicID=1403.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1403.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1403.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub94.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><se